The paper deals with using deep learning for MRI fingerprinting, which involves identifying tissue parameters from MRI signals. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper introduces a new complex-valued neural network with new activation functions, which could also fall under information theory (cs.IT).
